  "text": "We report a simple subcellular fractionation technique that is applicable to all the selected tissues. In uninfected animals tissue weights vary with time and in some, but not all, scrapie models there is a substantial loss of tissue weight in terminally affected animals which makes quantitative comparisons of PrP s~ on a tissue weight basis difficult (Outram, 1972; [CITATION_1] . For this reason the presence of PrP s~ was assessed by loading lanes with material equivalent to 50 or 25 % of the total wet weight. The use of a high titre polyclonal rabbit antimouse PrP antiserum gave a degree of sensitivity on immunoblotting which has allowed individual animals to be assayed for PrP s°. After proteinase K treatment immunoblots of all tissues displayed the same PrP polypeptide profile and M r values as those found for brain (Hope et al., 1988a; [CITATION_2] Farquhar et al., , 1990 .",
